comment: This rumor is a smear campaign on legitimate causes imo. Yes AH was lying. Yes Elon Musk paid off the ACLU to cover for himself. Yes the ACLU is corrupt enough to take the money and run with the lie. That said, when you start bringing in every activist who supported a certain law and claiming that they're corrupt, you clearly have an agenda too. Chanel Miller was telling the truth. Brock Turner was caught in the act. She tried to keep her identity private at first, because she's a real victim. The VAWA could be helpful in cases like hers. Even if you don't support that law, you don't need to smear everyone who has anything to do with it. Some of these people honestly believed AH at first because the whole story wasn't out there. By the way, her case did Not depend on the VAWA at all. It was no longer in effect when that article ran. All the protections that law was supposed to support were in place when she made her false report. That's why we're so sure it's false.
